The covariantized supersymmetry transformation laws remain unmodified.
Note that (in the absence of tensor multiplets)
such  an  Yang-Mills-Einstein supergravity theory
has no scalar potential, i.e., the ground states are Minkowski space-times.



The complete list
of 5D,    unified Yang-Mills-Einstein
  supergravity theories 
While we did not give a completeness proof of our list of unified MESGTs,
we are able to give a complete list of all possible
   unified   YMESGTs in
 five dimensions. This completeness proof is actually rather simple.
In a unified YMESGT, the vector fields  (and with them
the embedding coordinates ) transform, by definition,
 in the adjoint representation of a
simple group . The tensor  of the supergravity theory
then has to be a symmetric cubic
invariant of the adjoint representation of . Of all the simple groups,
only the unitary groups   and
their  different real forms  have such an invariant, namely the Gell-Mann
