As mentioned earlier, a YMESGT without tensor or hypermultiplets 
does not have a scalar potential. This means
that the vacuum expectation values (vevs) of the scalar fields 
 (or equivalently the vevs of the fields
) are not fixed. A vev  
corresponding to a compact direction in the
