Thus, almost all of the novel theories have non-homogeneous scalar manifolds.
Nevertheless, some of these
 non-homogeneous spaces can be  related  to homogeneous spaces in  an
interesting way that resembles an old construction by E. Cartan.
More explicitly, consider   the
